			"previous": " In 1939 a group of Hungarian scientists that included migr physicist Le Szil rd attempted to alert Washington of ongoing Nazi atomic bomb research The group s warnings were discounted 80 Einstein and Szil rd along with other refugees such as Edward Teller and Eugene Wigner regarded it as their responsibility to alert Americans to the possibility that German scientists might win the race to build an atomic bomb and to warn that Hitler would be more than willing to resort to such a weapon 81 82 ",
